1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:06,448
[One year ago]
<i>And the final member joining Wakers is...</i>

2
00:00:06,448 --> 00:00:09,834
<i>Trainee Kim Hyun Jae, congratulations.</i>

3
00:00:09,834 --> 00:00:12,959
<i>The idol survival show, Next Stage.</i>

4
00:00:12,959 --> 00:00:14,139
<i>The last of Wakers...</i>

5
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:16,433
Hyun Jae, congrats.

6
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,000
<i>Even before the show kicked off...</i>

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,209
I'll debut too, no matter what.

8
00:00:20,209 --> 00:00:22,167
Make sure we see each other again.

9
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:23,834
Yeah.

10
00:00:23,834 --> 00:00:25,939
We'll meet again for sure.

11
00:00:27,209 --> 00:00:29,083
- Call me...
- Stay in touch...

12
00:00:29,083 --> 00:00:30,751
<i>With outstanding skill and stage presence...</i>

13
00:00:30,751 --> 00:00:32,834
Mind if I keep in touch?

14
00:00:32,834 --> 00:00:35,042
<i>The sixth member of Wakers...</i>

15
00:00:35,042 --> 00:00:36,995
- Yeah, of course.
<i>- Trainee Kim Hyun Jae...</i>

16
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:39,834
<i>One more round of applause, please.</i>

17
00:00:39,834 --> 00:00:41,916
Congrats.

18
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,709
You did well.

19
00:00:46,709 --> 00:00:50,675
<i>Now let's hear a few words
from trainee Kim Hyun Jae.</i>

20
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,685
Hyun Jae!

21
00:00:59,685 --> 00:01:01,905
What are you doing here?

22
00:01:01,905 --> 00:01:03,855
Ditched practice.

23
00:01:04,523 --> 00:01:05,685
Is that okay?

24
00:01:05,685 --> 00:01:08,777
Things kick off tomorrow and it'll get crazy,

25
00:01:10,105 --> 00:01:12,489
so I wanted to see your face before that.

26
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:17,536
Well, you saw it, so you're good.

27
00:01:17,536 --> 00:01:19,403
Anything else?

28
00:01:22,792 --> 00:01:23,925
Nope.

29
00:01:23,925 --> 00:01:25,525
That's it.

30
00:01:25,525 --> 00:01:28,247
Then head back before I call your agency.

31
00:01:33,876 --> 00:01:35,512
Hyun Jae!

32
00:01:36,876 --> 00:01:38,765
Knock it out of the park.

33
00:01:39,459 --> 00:01:40,813
You got this!

34
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:14,436
<i>This one's a hit.</i>

35
00:02:14,436 --> 00:02:15,677
<i>Almost fell for you.</i>

36
00:02:15,677 --> 00:02:17,667
<i>Whatever.</i>

37
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:19,988
<i>They really won't give me a break.</i>

38
00:02:19,988 --> 00:02:22,847
<i>Looks like they're squeezing every penny
out of us this year.</i>

39
00:02:22,847 --> 00:02:24,853
<i>They're ruthless.</i>

40
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:26,547
<i>You feeling okay?</i>

41
00:02:26,547 --> 00:02:29,387
<i>I'm fine. How about you, holding up?</i>

42
00:02:29,387 --> 00:02:33,083
<i>I've got fans now,
the agency's backing me up...</i>

43
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:34,863
<i>Debut might be around the corner.</i>

44
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:38,048
<i>We'll share a stage soon, so brace yourself.</i>

45
00:02:38,709 --> 00:02:41,578
<i>Will do. I'll be waiting for it.</i>

46
00:02:58,011 --> 00:02:59,000
[What's up?]

47
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,430
<i>Finally wrapped.</i>

48
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:01,932
<i>You done?</i>

49
00:03:01,932 --> 00:03:03,334
<i>Yeah.</i>

50
00:03:03,334 --> 00:03:05,751
<i>Did I wake you up this late?</i>

51
00:03:05,751 --> 00:03:06,979
<i>No, just...</i>

52
00:03:06,979 --> 00:03:10,857
<i>Practicing, also waiting for your reply.</i>

53
00:03:11,751 --> 00:03:14,255
<i>You were practicing?</i>

54
00:03:14,255 --> 00:03:15,834
<i>That's rough.</i>

55
00:03:15,834 --> 00:03:17,656
<i>No way, you've got it way harder.</i>

56
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:19,406
<i>Pretty exhausting, right?</i>

57
00:03:19,406 --> 00:03:22,077
<i>You must be wiped. Go to bed.</i>

58
00:03:22,077 --> 00:03:23,375
<i>You too.</i>

59
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:24,913
<i>Sleep tight.</i>

60
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:37,537
[Did you eat?]

61
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:43,925
Hey, should I try out for a girl group too?

62
00:03:45,918 --> 00:03:48,520
Who am I even talking to?

63
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:56,371
Why wait around? Just send it yourself!

64
00:03:56,371 --> 00:03:57,779
On second thought, I'll do it!

65
00:03:57,779 --> 00:03:59,855
Give it to me!

66
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:12,878
[Miss you, Hyun Jae. Don't you miss me?]

67
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:23,430
<i>Hey, Soo An, are you practicing?</i>

68
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,140
<i>Sorry to say this, but...</i>

69
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:29,058
<i>the debut lineup timing we discussed
is getting pushed back.</i>

70
00:04:29,058 --> 00:04:31,021
<i>Things are tight at the company.</i>

71
00:04:31,021 --> 00:04:34,399
<i>The CEO is out chasing new investors right now.</i>

72
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,859
<i>So just hang in there.</i>

73
00:04:35,859 --> 00:04:37,334
Okay.

74
00:04:37,334 --> 00:04:39,571
Got it.

75
00:04:39,571 --> 00:04:40,864
<i>And as for practice...</i>

76
00:04:40,864 --> 00:04:43,659
<i>you should take a break starting tomorrow.</i>

77
00:04:43,659 --> 00:04:44,660
Sorry?

78
00:04:44,660 --> 00:04:47,696
<i>We couldn't renew the studio lease.</i>

79
00:04:47,696 --> 00:04:50,791
<i>I'll let you know once we find a new place.</i>

80
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,292
Okay.

81
00:05:07,224 --> 00:05:09,935
<i>- Waker! Hi, we're Wakers.
- Waker! Hi, we're Wakers.</i>

82
00:05:09,935 --> 00:05:13,605
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

83
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:23,390
[Miss you, Hyun Jae. Don't you miss me?]

84
00:05:27,286 --> 00:05:32,820
[You're busy... I'm bu...]

85
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:36,587
<i>Hyun Jae, congrats.</i>

86
00:05:36,587 --> 00:05:38,297
<i>I'll debut too, no matter what.</i>

87
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:40,042
<i>Make sure we see each other again.</i>

88
00:05:40,042 --> 00:05:42,301
<i>Things are tight at the company.</i>

89
00:05:42,301 --> 00:05:45,345
[Caller Blocked]
<i>We couldn't renew the studio lease.</i>

90
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:47,960
[Contact Blocked]
<i>It seems like...</i>

91
00:05:58,901 --> 00:06:00,988
[Mom]

92
00:06:04,031 --> 00:06:06,334
I shook off all those pipe dreams, as you said.

93
00:06:06,334 --> 00:06:08,785
I'm working hard. Don't worry.

94
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,371
Yeah.

95
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:13,331
Yeah, I will.

96
00:06:14,834 --> 00:06:17,168
Okay, bye.

97
00:06:24,834 --> 00:06:26,886
Gone cold already.

98
00:06:34,167 --> 00:06:35,895
<i>You a zombie?</i>

99
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,649
<i>Done with practice?</i>

100
00:06:38,649 --> 00:06:39,697
[Kim Hyun Jae]

101
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:43,459
<i>Ugh, it's cold.</i>

102
00:06:43,459 --> 00:06:44,946
<i>Drink it anyway.</i>

103
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:47,032
<i>You said you can't wake up lately.</i>

104
00:06:48,417 --> 00:06:51,585
<i>Coffee tastes best when it's hot.</i>

105
00:06:51,585 --> 00:06:53,496
<i>Want me to warm it up?</i>

106
00:07:08,626 --> 00:07:09,751
<i>Hey!</i>

107
00:07:09,751 --> 00:07:11,153
<i>Someone might walk in!</i>

108
00:07:11,153 --> 00:07:13,062
<i>Nobody's coming. We're fine.</i>

109
00:07:13,062 --> 00:07:15,143
<i>No, I smell like sweat.</i>

110
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,250
<i>You don't.</i>

111
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:19,356
<i>Just hold on like this.</i>

112
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:21,852
<i>Just a moment.</i>

113
00:07:25,792 --> 00:07:27,697
<i>Warm now, right?</i>

114
00:07:44,893 --> 00:07:46,550
This isn't right...

115
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:47,912
[Hotel LUXE]

116
00:07:53,292 --> 00:07:54,773
You can pay me back...

117
00:07:54,773 --> 00:07:56,393
with your body.

118
00:07:59,709 --> 00:08:02,357
What is going through his head?

119
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:09,906
This is awkward. Let's head in.

120
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:19,040
What? You're the one who wanted this.

121
00:08:23,378 --> 00:08:26,523
It looks rough out here,
but inside should be fine.

122
00:08:27,584 --> 00:08:29,635
People are giving us weird looks,

123
00:08:29,635 --> 00:08:31,025
hurry up.

124
00:08:39,728 --> 00:08:41,500
What?

125
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:43,898
You booked it ahead?

126
00:08:46,109 --> 00:08:49,488
You don't look the type,
but you're really thirsty.

127
00:08:49,488 --> 00:08:52,241
Is this really happening?

128
00:08:52,241 --> 00:08:53,271
Hey!

129
00:08:53,271 --> 00:08:54,951
Wait up!

130
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:20,060
What was I even thinking?

131
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:22,173
What brings you here all of a sudden?

132
00:09:25,459 --> 00:09:27,611
If you've got nothing to say, I'm out.

133
00:09:27,611 --> 00:09:29,235
This.

134
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:32,978
Didn't you leave it for me to see?

135
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:50,507
Why'd you cut off contact?

136
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:52,009
Cut off?

137
00:09:55,459 --> 00:09:57,180
Forget it.

138
00:09:59,626 --> 00:10:02,311
We're not the kind to keep in touch anyway.

139
00:10:02,311 --> 00:10:03,606
Then what are we to each other?

140
00:10:03,606 --> 00:10:05,772
Business.

141
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,399
We used each other to get noticed.

142
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:09,859
You debuted, so isn't that enough?

143
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:10,861
What?

144
00:10:10,861 --> 00:10:13,459
The whole thing was staged.

145
00:10:13,459 --> 00:10:15,407
What more could there be?

146
00:10:18,994 --> 00:10:21,454
You really feel nothing for me?

147
00:11:16,057 --> 00:11:17,344
In Korea,

148
00:11:17,344 --> 00:11:19,721
there's a tradition when you move in.

149
00:11:32,542 --> 00:11:34,361
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

150
00:11:44,439 --> 00:11:45,652
What?

151
00:11:45,652 --> 00:11:48,124
Nothing, you just chug it down.

152
00:11:48,876 --> 00:11:53,630
First glass is one shot in Korea, right?

153
00:11:54,961 --> 00:11:58,597
Some wonderful person taught me that.

154
00:12:13,638 --> 00:12:15,439
Tastes good.

155
00:12:16,278 --> 00:12:17,613
Why are you drinking so fast?

156
00:12:17,613 --> 00:12:19,406
Are you a heavy drinker?

157
00:12:20,709 --> 00:12:22,743
I don't know.

158
00:12:22,743 --> 00:12:25,412
You don't usually drink much,
because it's a Buddhist country?

159
00:12:25,412 --> 00:12:26,978
Buddhism?

160
00:12:26,978 --> 00:12:28,014
No.

161
00:12:28,014 --> 00:12:29,840
I drink like hell.

162
00:12:30,792 --> 00:12:32,419
You learned all the wrong words.

163
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:34,838
Pretty damn good, right?

164
00:12:34,838 --> 00:12:36,965
Yeah. Damn good.

165
00:12:36,965 --> 00:12:40,118
But that's a bad word in Korea.

166
00:12:40,118 --> 00:12:42,679
You're speaking casually, too.

167
00:12:45,218 --> 00:12:47,341
You're Korean, aren't you?

168
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:52,188
Pouring your own is bad luck.

169
00:13:00,656 --> 00:13:03,105
I can't leave any drops...

170
00:13:22,219 --> 00:13:24,701
You really feel nothing for me?

171
00:13:49,913 --> 00:13:52,629
I was worried something might still linger.

172
00:13:53,709 --> 00:13:55,794
Good thing there's nothing.

173
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,845
[Episode 4 Preview]

174
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:06,972
This is crazy!

175
00:14:06,972 --> 00:14:09,057
Why can't I remember anything?

176
00:14:09,057 --> 00:14:10,398
Sleep well?

177
00:14:10,398 --> 00:14:11,476
You...

178
00:14:11,476 --> 00:14:13,729
Did I say anything weird?

179
00:14:13,729 --> 00:14:15,167
I don't know.

180
00:14:15,167 --> 00:14:16,648
I can't speak Korean.

181
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:18,650
Haven't you milked me enough for business?

182
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:19,792
Got more uses for me lined up?

183
00:14:19,792 --> 00:14:21,236
Right.

184
00:14:21,959 --> 00:14:23,488
Want me to sleep with you too?

185
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:25,824
Don't ever show your face again.

186
00:14:27,626 --> 00:14:28,577
Fine.

187
00:14:28,577 --> 00:14:30,537
If that's what you want.

